/F1 16 Tf
(What is Agentic AI?) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(Agentic AI describes artificial intelligence systems that are designed to autonomously make) Tj
0 -15 Td
(decisions and take actions to achieve specific goals with limited human intervention. Unlike) Tj
0 -15 Td
(traditional generative AI that primarily responds to prompts, agentic AI systems can:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Operate autonomously over extended periods) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Make decisions based on context and available information) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Plan and execute multi-step tasks) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Learn from interactions and improve performance over time) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Adapt to changing environments and requirements) Tj
0 -30 Td
/F1 16 Tf
(Key Capabilities of Agentic AI) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(1. Autonomous Decision-Making: Agentic AI can evaluate options and make decisions without) Tj
0 -15 Td
(   requiring human input for each step.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(2. Goal-Oriented Behavior: These systems can understand complex goals and develop plans) Tj
0 -15 Td
(   to achieve them, adjusting strategies as needed.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(3. Environmental Awareness: Agentic AI can perceive and interpret its environment, whether) Tj
0 -15 Td
(   digital or physical, to inform its actions.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(4. Memory and Learning: These systems can retain information from past interactions and) Tj
0 -15 Td
(   improve their performance through experience.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(5. Tool Utilization: Advanced agentic systems can use external tools and APIs to extend) Tj
0 -15 Td
(   their capabilities and accomplish more complex tasks.) Tj
0 -30 Td
/F1 16 Tf
(Applications of Agentic AI) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(Agentic AI has numerous potential applications across various industries:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Business Process Automation: Handling complex workflows that require decision-making) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Customer Service: Managing customer interactions with minimal human intervention) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Research and Development: Conducting experiments and analyzing results autonomously) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Personal Assistance: Managing schedules, communications, and tasks proactively) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Healthcare: Monitoring patient data and suggesting interventions) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Finance: Analyzing market trends and executing trading strategies) Tj
0 -30 Td
/F1 16 Tf
(Challenges and Considerations) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(While agentic AI offers significant benefits, several challenges must be addressed:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Alignment: Ensuring AI agents act in accordance with human values and intentions) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Safety: Preventing harmful actions or unintended consequences) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Transparency: Understanding how and why agents make specific decisions) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Control: Maintaining appropriate human oversight and intervention capabilities) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Privacy: Managing access to sensitive information) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Security: Protecting against manipulation or misuse) Tj
0 -30 Td
/F1 16 Tf
(The Future of Agentic AI) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(As agentic AI continues to evolve, we can expect:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Increased autonomy and capability in handling complex tasks) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Better integration with existing systems and workflows) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- More sophisticated reasoning and problem-solving abilities) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- Enhanced collaboration between human workers and AI agents) Tj
0 -15 Td
(- New regulatory frameworks to govern agentic systems) Tj
0 -30 Td
